<br>
How are current and future zones/mobs balanced with these new items.<br>
Focus items seem like a gameplay tuning nightmare because you either design them so their effects are minimal (not really contributing to 'balance', just giving the false sense they are) or they are made stronger which may make current/future encounters trivial and may have to be retuned or made harder had the items not existed which leaves you back where you started.<br>
<br>
Can you do 1 more quad on your wizard because you have focus items for mana preservation and range which helps keep you alive and avoid deaths better?<br>
<br>
Casters since the patch are now weaker if you consider the upgrade to caster npc's. If any caster class is now more in demand its going to be enchanters (like they needed more reasons to be picked for a group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) to quickly mez/stun the crap out of any casters that get pulled so they dont mez or AoE the crap out of you.<br>
<br>
The same froglok ilis wizard people killed a week ago now tosses ice comets in their face and you still get the same damn amount of xp. Noone's bitching of course because they all think they are mad uber now with these new focus effects. The items are still weak if you compare a focus3 item to stuff like fungi tunic on a melee.<br>
<br>
There are some focus item effects are nice (reagent conservation 3 = less peridots used by my cleric) but I don't recall my cleric actually hurting for 'caster balance' like my mage and wizard are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Some of the effects on the focus items i'm seeing are about as useful or as powerful as CHA on my warriors armor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have to agree with others that they made too many focus types which creates a false sense of complexity and really screws with 'what caster should get this item' because people will weigh the focus effect more heavily than the other stats when in some cases it shouldn't.<br>
<br>
I think verant is trying too hard to come up with new gameplay/item angles and creating excess complexity where it is not needed that borders on tedious.<br>
<br>
An example of tedium being swapping in an rmb on my cleric whenever she uses symbol(for a chance at not using the peridot) because her normal bracers without the focus effect are better for normal use.<br>
<br>
Just some rambling for someone that wants a good reason to un retire her wizard and mage that doesn't revolve around focus items<br>
