-Ikeya <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubeingofpureego.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Being of Pure Ego</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/02 6:41:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1191.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish...</span><hr size=1> I think people are looking at focus items in the wrong way.  They are only one aspect of caster balance, not the end-all of it.  The particular issue they were trying to address with focus items is the disparity between the level 60 caster that spends a lot of time getting nice gear versus the level 60 melee who does the same.  A level 60 rogue with Ntov/Luclin weapons is *way* more effective then a 60 rogue with RB/kunark/velious weapons.  A level 60 wizard with ntov/luclin stuff is marginally better (although AA abilities help a lot, it still just rewards leveling pretty much exclusively). By putting these focus on difficult encounters, they allow casters to actually have something to look forward to.<br>
<br>
That being said I don't think the implementation is quite right.  I wouldve suggested using level limits and percentage differences.  The level limit would determine what level dungeon you would get it, and the percentage would indicate the difficulty of that dungeon relative to your level.<br>
<br>
So the low level, low percentage would be easy to get.  Maybe even put it on the newbie quests.  The higher percentage low level focus would then be put in dungeons. Thus, the low level who spent time collecting nice gear would actually be better off then the one who just tries to level as fast as possible.<br>
<br>
The same would be true of the higer level focus.  Low percentage would drop in seb/HS/chardok/velks/etc.  The higher percentage ones would drop off raid level mobs.  <br>
<br>
This is over simplified, I would do more then just 2 different percentages, but you get the point. <br>
<br>
Alright, thats the end of my &quot;if I were a game designer&quot; speech. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umacfudd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Macfudd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/02 6:50:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1191.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well...</span><hr size=1> I think Rombus kinda summed it up fairly well.  I'm fairly casual in my playing myself, don't stress on the focus.<br>
