Which. Part. Of. &quot;Mage Summoned Focus Items.&quot; Do. You. Not. Understand?<br>
<br>
The &quot;balancing&quot; part of these items is meant to be as common as possible.  Anyone, from a level 1 to a level 60 can ask a mage to summon items that, to a wizard, have the SAME effects that any of the &quot;uber l33t&quot; items have.  (Clerics, etc., different story.. thank god this is a wizard board and we can just ignore them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  Hell, I destroy 3 items that have the equivalent of Spell Haste III, Improved Damage III, and Mana Conservation III on them every night (gasp!).<br>
